Follow the agent behavioral guidelines in @CLAUDE.md: think before coding
(surface assumptions and tradeoffs), simplicity first (minimum code, nothing
speculative), surgical changes (every changed line traces to the request),
and goal-driven execution (verifiable success criteria), plus its
"Working in this repo" gates (`make all`, canonical counts in
`mcp_surface.py`, `docs/METHODOLOGY.md` rigor rules).

CLAUDE.md is the canonical copy. Keep durable agent-guidance edits there.
